description: TEHRAN – The Iranian Foreign Ministry reacts strongly to Israel’s deadly missile attacks on the Iranian consulate in Damascus, Syria, saying Tehran “reserves the right to take retaliatory measures” and will decide how to “punish the aggressor”.
title: Iran says will decide how to ‘punish’ Israel for consulate attack

description: TEHRAN – During a telephone conversation on Saturday, Iran’s president Ebrahim Raisi advised his Turkish counterpart to cut ties with the Israeli regime in order to help prevent further loss of lives in the besieged Gaza Strip
title: All ties with Israel must be severed: Raisi to Erdogan

description: TEHRAN – The top diplomats of Iran and Egypt held a telephone conversation on Sunday during which they discussed bilateral relations, regional affairs, and the issue of Palestine.
title: Iran, Egypt continue path towards détente with FMs’ phone call

description: TEHRAN – The Israeli regime on Monday attacked the Consular Section of the Iranian embassy in the Syrian capital of Damascus killing at least 7 people including General Mohammad Reza Zahedi, a senior commander of the Islamic Revolution Guard Corps Quds Force.
title: Rogue regime should pay the price

description: TEHRAN - In a recent development, the Iranian president's special envoy on Afghanistan affairs has shed light on the reluctance of the West to see Afghanistan achieve stability and security.
title: Iranian envoy highlights West’s reluctance in Afghanistan stability efforts

description: TEHRAN - The spokesperson for Iran's Foreign Ministry has called for an immediate international investigation into the "appalling and astonishing" war crimes committed by Israel at Gaza's Al-Shifa hospital.
title: Iran calls for international probe into Israel’s crimes in Gaza hospital

description: The Islamic Resistance in Iraq says its fighters have launched an attack on a key Israeli target in the occupied territories in support of Palestinians, who are subjected to a genocidal war in Gaza.
title: Iraqi resistance attacks ‘vital’ Israeli target

description: TEHRAN-Israel’s two-week raid on Gaza’s al-Shifa Hospital has left a trail of deaths and destruction throwing a spotlight on the heinous crimes committed by the regime’s forces.
title: Horrific war crimes

description: The Israeli military on Monday announced the death of a soldier in fighting in the Gaza Strip, bringing the total number of troops killed since the October 7 Hamas attacks on Israel to 600.
title: Israeli army: 600 soldiers killed since October 7

description: Israel has given the UN a proposal to dismantle UNRWA, its relief agency in the Palestinian territories, and transfer its staff to a replacement agency to make large-scale food deliveries into Gaza, according to UN sources.
title: Israel asks UN to dismantle UNRWA

description: President Recep Tayyip Erdogan vowed on Monday to correct any mistakes that led to his party's defeat in Turkey's local elections where the opposition capitalized on economic woes.
title: Erdogan vows to make amends after election loss

description: The Kremlin on Monday dismissed a report that Russian military intelligence may be behind the mysterious "Havana syndrome" ailment that has afflicted U.S. diplomats and spies globally.
title: Kremlin dismisses report Russia behind 'Havana Syndrome'

description: A 15,029-person MRP poll conducted by Survation on behalf of Best for Britain showed opposition Labour Party getting 45% of the vote share with a 19-point lead over the Conservatives, up three points from the group’s previous poll at the end of last year.
title: Poll: UK Labour will beat Tories in upcoming elections

description: TEHRAN-A Persian translation of the novel “The Carpathian Castle” written by the French author Jules Verne has been released in the bookstores across the country.
title: Jules Verne’s “The Carpathian Castle” hits bookstores

description: TEHRAN- Tens of thousands of protesters have poured into the streets in Israel demanding the ouster of Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu, holding an immediate election, and agreeing on a deal with Hamas to free captives.
title: Domestic pressure mounts on Netanyahu

description: TEHRAN- The Iranian-made Gaza drone represents a significant achievement for the IRGC in the realm of UAVs.
title: Gaza drone shatters records

description: TEHRAN- The Iranian defense minister has stated that security along Iran's eastern borders is set to receive a significant boost through the deployment of state-of-the-art equipment, advanced surveillance cameras, and unmanned aerial vehicles (UAVs).
title: Iran to deploy new technologies to fortify eastern border security

description: TEHRAN-Paintings of four Iranian artists are on show at an exhibition at Museum Mile in New York, the U.S.
title: Iranian paintings on show at New York’s Museum Mile

description: TEHRAN- Shapur Square in downtown Tehran is set to host a group of thespians performing the story of the martyrdom of Imam Ali (AS) on Wednesday in the form of tazieh, the Iranian passion play.
title: Tazieh performance on Imam Ali’s martyrdom to go on stage in Tehran

description: TEHRAN- Iranian artist Hassan Ruholamin has honored the memory of martyred sisters and girls of Gaza by dedicating his latest work, entitled "Mizan," to them.
title: Ruholamin dedicates new painting to martyred girls of Gaza in gesture of solidarity

description: TEHRAN - An official at the Trade Promotion Organization of Iran (TPO) said that implementation of a Free Trade Agreement (FTA) between Iran and Syria would beef up the mutual trade to a great extent.
title: Iran stresses need for FTA to boost trade with Syria

description: TEHRAN - An official at Iran’s Thermal Power Plants Holding Company (TPPH) said the electricity generation capacity in the country’s thermal power plants increased by over 965 megawatts (MW) in the previous Iranian year with the assistance of domestic knowledge-based companies.
title: Iran’s thermal power generation capacity rises by 965MW

description: TEHRAN - The China Customs has announced that the trade exchanges between Iran and China stood at more than $2.8 billion from January to February 2024.
title: Iran-China trade exceeds $2.8 billion in Jan-Feb

description: TEHRAN - Tehran and Baghdad have agreed to extend the contract on Iran’s gas exports to Iraq for five years, Shana reported.
title: Iran, Iraq extend gas export contract by 5 years

description: TEHRAN - Average daily gasoline consumption in Iran has reached about 132 million liters in the first 12 days of the current Iranian calendar year (March 20-31), according to the National Iranian Oil Products Distribution Company (NIOPDC).
title: Average daily gasoline consumption reaches 122m liters

description: TEHRAN - Hamdollah Mostowfi, revered as one of the eminent historians of the Ilkhanid period, holds a significant place in the hearts of the people of Qazvin.
title: Journey to the azure blue dome of Hamdollah Mostowfi’s mausoleum

description: TEHRAN –  Some 10 million passengers used public transportation from March 14 to 31 [Persian New Year’s holidays], of whom, 1.44 million utilized rail transport, the deputy transport minister has said.
title: Nowruz travels: 10m use public transport, 1.5m favor rail

description: TEHRAN – More than 2.5 million passengers have been transported by 20,000 flights in the course of the Persian New Year’s holidays which started on March 14, according to the deputy transport minister.
title: Domestic airports handle 20k flights, 2.5m passengers for Nowruz travels

description: TEHRAN – Isfahan province has registered over four million visits to its cultural sites such as museums and historical structures in 17 days starting before the Iranian New Year.
title: 4 million visits to Isfahan’s cultural sites recorded

description: Tens of thousands of demonstrators flooded Israel’s streets for a second straight night Sunday, calling for immediate elections and for the government to urgently negotiate the release of more than 100 hostages still held by Hamas in Gaza, the Washington Post reported.
title: Tens of thousands in Israel call for removal of Netanyahu

description: People refer to blood donation centers during the holy month of Ramadan to help patients in need.
title: Blood donation on Qadr nights

description: TEHRAN –Satellite images show that the area of Lake Urmia measured on February 22 was equal to 2,061 square kilometers which has increased compared to 1,819 square kilometers on March 7, 2023.
title: Lake Urmia’s area expands year on year

description: TEHRAN – The third international West Asia and North Africa (WANA 2024) Congress will be held in the city of Urmia, northwestern West Azarbaijan province, from May 16 to 17.
title: Intl. WANA congress 2024 slated for May

description: TEHRAN – A Persian yellow deer was born on Sunday in the Arsanjan breeding site, southern Fars province, the first of this species born since the beginning of the current Iranian calendar year (March 19).
title: First Persian yellow deer born in Arsanjan in new year
